{{redirect |Tabu language|Tabu dialect |Konyak language }} {{Infobox language |name=Elseng |nativename=Morwap |region=[[Papua (Indonesian province)|Papua]], [[Indonesia]] |speakers=300 |date=1991 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Papuan |fam1=[[Border languages (New Guinea)|Border]] ? |iso3=mrf |glotto=else1239 |glottorefname=Elseng }}
'''Elseng''' (Morwap) is a poorly documented [[Papuan languages|Papuan language]] spoken by about 300 people (in 1991) in the [[Indonesia]]n province of [[Papua (Indonesian province)|Papua]]. It is also known as '''Morwap''', which means "what is it?"
Laycock classified Elseng as a [[language isolate]], but noted pronominal similarities with the [[Border languages (New Guinea)|Border languages]]. Ross included it in Border because of these similarities, but noted that it does not appear to share any lexical similarities with the family. However, this may be an effect of the paucity of data on Elseng.
