'''Iberophone '''or''' Pan-Iberian space'''<ref>http://www.oei.es/noticias/spip.php?article15076</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.linhadireta.com.br/revistas/arquivos/heuyzr2upui2.pdf |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2016-02-28 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150926045614/http://www.linhadireta.com.br/revistas/arquivos/heuyzr2upui2.pdf |archivedate=2015-09-26 |df= }}</ref><ref>http://isdiber.org/paniberismo-e-iberofonia-2/</ref><ref>http://lusopresse.com/2011/254/GeoLingua.aspx</ref><ref>http://www25.senado.leg.br/web/atividade/notas-taquigraficas/-/notas/r/4398</ref> ('''''Iberofonía''''' or '''''espacio iberófono o panibérico''''' in Spanish, '''''Iberofonia''''' or '''''espaço iberófono ou panibérico''''' in Portuguese) is a neologism used to designate the [[Iberian Romance languages]]-speaking countries, mainly [[Spanish language|Spanish]] and [[Portuguese language|Portuguese.]]<ref>http://eprints.ucm.es/24644/1/T35176.pdf</ref><ref>http://isdiber.org/paniberismo-e-iberofonia-2/</ref> In this sense, it includes the [[Hispanophone]] and [[Lusophone]] communities: [[Ibero-America]], plus the Spanish and Portuguese speaking countries in Europe, Africa and Asia, comprising the whole of the [[Community of Portuguese Language Countries]]. The terms "'''Luso-Hispanic world"''',<ref>http://escholarship.org/uc/ssha_transmodernity</ref> "'''multinational space of Iberian languages-speaking countries'''" and "'''Afro-Iberian-Latin American space'''" have also been used.<ref>http://www.fundeu.es/noticia/experto-destaca-el-potencial-internacional-de-un-espacio-iberoparlante/</ref><ref>http://isdiber.org/comunidades-multinacionales-iberofonas-existentes-la-comunidad-iberoamericana-de-naciones-y-la-comunidad-de-paises-de-lengua-portuguesa/</ref><ref>http://eprints.ucm.es/24644/1/T35176.pdf</ref><ref>http://www.cepese.pt/portal/pt/investigacao/working-papers/relacoes-externas-de-portugal/espaco-afro-ibero-latino-americano-geopolitica-geoestrategia-e-importancia-para-a-lusofonia/Espaco-Afro-Ibero-Latino-Americano-geopolitica.pdf</ref>
