'''Maarten Hamckema''' ({{circa|1550}}, [[Follega]] – 1620), sometimes [[Anglicisation|anglicized]] as '''Marten Hamkes''' and mainly known by his [[pen name]] '''Martinus Hamconius''', was a Frisian writer, poet and historian best known for his [[apocryphal]] [[history]] books on the [[Kingdom of Frisia]].

